headline: How Securing a Major AI Client for 18A Chips At Intel (INTC) Has Changed Its Investment Story
summary: Industry sources reported in the past week that Intel’s foundry division has secured a significant artificial intelligence client, likely Microsoft, for its advanced 18A/AP chip manufacturing process, marking important progress for the company’s external customer strategy. This development signals that Intel is gaining traction in advanced chip manufacturing for AI applications, highlighting a tangible step forward in its efforts to compete with established players in the semiconductor...
